{"id":1077,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1077,"title":"Saul","subtitle":"","short_title":"Saul","uri":"/scriptures/bd/saul","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/saul.t1","order":".000.3560"},[".title","Saul"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/saul.p1","order":".000.3561"},["i","Asked."],"(1) Son of Kish and first king of Israel; his appointment (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/9.1?span=9.1-10.27"},"1 Sam. 9:1–10:27"],"); leads against Nahash (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/11"},"1 Sam. 11"],"); offers sacrifice (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/13.9"},"13:9"],"); his oath (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/14.24-45"},"14:24–45"],"); war against Amalekites (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/15.1-9"},"15:1–9"],"); rejected from being king (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/15.23"},"15:23"],"); dealings with David (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/16.14?span=16.14-19.10"},"16:14–19:10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/23.24?span=23.24-26.25"},"23:24–26:25"],"); slays priests of Nob (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/22.6-19"},"22:6–19"],"); his death (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/28?span=28-31"},"1 Sam. 28–31"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/1"},"2 Sam. 1"],"); his burial (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/21.12-14"},"2 Sam. 21:12–14"],"). Saul’s downfall shows the consequences of uncontrolled self-will and disobedience to counsel."],["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/scriptures/bd/saul.p2","order":".000.3562"},"(2) The original Jewish name of the Apostle Paul; he is so called up to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.9"},"Acts 13:9"],"."]]],"refs":null}
